  "prompt": "Are there specific laws targeting money laundering?",
  "response": "Many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes. These typically include:\n\n1. Requirements for financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement compliance programs\n\n2. Legal frameworks like:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act (various countries)\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n\n3. Potential penalties including:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial fines\n- Asset seizure\n- Business license revocation\n\nThese laws aim to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income.\n\nWould you like me to provide more specific details about money laundering legislation?",
